to the editor while the increased abortion training in ob gyn residencies newest skill for future ob gyns abortion training june 11 is a positive step toward increasing access to it this training itself will not increase the number of doctors providing abortions besides concerns about violence and harassment other factors often discourage newly trained physicians from providing abortions among them are difficulty obtaining malpractice coverage for this procedure the sometimes cumbersome abortion restrictions that vary by state and the contracts physicians must sign explicitly forbidding abortions when they join certain group practices or affiliate with certain hospitals much remains to be done to ensure that abortion services are integrated into mainstream medical circles dr carole joffe davis calif

